;:&quot;https:\/\/secure-us.imrworldwide.com\/cgi-bin\/m?&quot;},{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;scCI&quot;,&quot;value&quot;:&quot;us-200330&quot;},{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;scC6&quot;,&quot;value&quot;:&quot;vc,c01&quot;}]},{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;MuxQOSPluginJS&quot;,&quot;category&quot;:&quot;qos&quot;,&quot;enabled&quot;:true,&quot;params&quot;:[{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;propertyKey&quot;,&quot;value&quot;:&quot;b7d6e48b7461a61cb6e863a62&quot;}]}],&quot;trackingAccount&quot;:&quot;cbsigamespotsite&quot;,&quot;trackingSiteCode&quot;:&quot;gs&quot;,&quot;trackingPrimaryId&quot;:&quot;cbsigamespotsite&quot;,&quot;videoAssetSource&quot;:&quot;GameSpot&quot;,&quot;uvpjsHostname&quot;:&quot;\/\/www.gamespot.com&quot;,&quot;siteType&quot;:&quot;responsive web&quot;,&quot;startMuted&quot;:false,&quot;screenMediumThumb&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/www.gamespot.com\/a\/uploads\/screen_medium\/1823\/18237460\/4379302-v1.jpg&quot;,&quot;videoStreams&quot;:{&quot;adaptive_stream&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/cdn.jwplayer.com\/manifests\/N5OUWJqJ.m3u8&quot;},&quot;userId&quot;:0,&quot;premium&quot;:false,&quot;datePublished&quot;:1728082740,&quot;videoAdPartner&quot;:&quot;desktop%2Fgamespot.com&quot;,&quot;videoAdMobilePartner&quot;:&quot;mobile_web%2Fgamespot.com_mobile&quot;}" data-non-iframe-embed="1" data-jw-context-name="gamespot" data-jw-media-id="N5OUWJqJ" data-jw-player-url="https://cdn.jwplayer.com/libraries/VXc5h4Tf.js" data-jw-video-token="" data-has-youtube="" data-youtube-icon-path="https://www.gamespot.com/a/bundles/phoenixsite/images/core/loose/icn-youtube-30x30.png" id="video-rectangle" data-embed-type="video" data-ref-id="2300-6465285" data-src="/videos/silent-hill-2-ps2-vs-silent-hill-2-remake-ps5-graphics-comparison/2300-6465285/" data-width="100%" data-height="100%" data-video-start="0"><div><p>Silent Hill 2 PS2 Vs Silent Hill 2 Remake PS5 Graphics Comparison</p><div><p>         Want us to remember this setting for all your devices?       </p><p><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/signup/">Sign up</a> or <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/login/">Sign in</a> now!       </p></div></div><p>       Please use a html5 video capable browser to watch videos.     </p><p>       This video has an invalid file format.     </p><p>Sorry, but you can't access this content!</p></div><p>If you want to spend Halloween slaying zombies, you have numerous solid options, including the bloody action-RPG <strong><a href="https://clicks.trx-hub.com/xid/fandom_32094_gamespot?q=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dpbolvw.net%2Fclick-100770772-13797872%3Fsid%3Dsubid_value%26url%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.fanatical.com%2Fen%2Fgame%2Fdead-island-2&amp;p=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamespot.com%2Farticles%2Fhorror-game-sale-features-scary-good-deals-on-silent-hill-2-cult-of-the-lamb-and-more%2F1100-6527424%2F%3Fftag%3DCAD-01-10abi2f&amp;event_type=click" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Dead Island 2</a></strong> for $22.49 (was $50). Aside from brutal combat and grotesque enemies, it gives you plenty of stats and gear to manage. Itâ€™s a great cooperative game, especially if you're looking for a fun way to spend your Halloween evening.</p><p>Then there's also PlayStation's not-zombie games <strong><a href="https://clicks.trx-hub.com/xid/fandom_32094_gamespot?q=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dpbolvw.net%2Fclick-100770772-13797872%3Fsid%3Dsubid_value%26url%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.fanatical.com%2Fen%2Fgame%2Fdays-gone&amp;p=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamespot.com%2Farticles%2Fhorror-game-sale-features-scary-good-deals-on-silent-hill-2-cult-of-the-lamb-and-more%2F1100-6527424%2F%3Fftag%3DCAD-01-10abi2f&amp;event_type=click" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Days Gone</a></strong> for $11.49 (was $50) and <strong><a href="https://clicks.trx-hub.com/xid/fandom_32094_gamespot?q=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tkqlhce.com%2Fclick-100770772-13797872%3Fsid%3Dsubid_value%26url%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.fanatical.com%2Fen%2Fgame%2Fthe-last-of-us-part-i&amp;p=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamespot.com%2Farticles%2Fhorror-game-sale-features-scary-good-deals-on-silent-hill-2-cult-of-the-lamb-and-more%2F1100-6527424%2F%3Fftag%3DCAD-01-10abi2f&amp;event_type=click" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">The Last of Us Part I</a></strong> for $32.39 (was $60). Days Gone's fast-moving, flesh-eating creatures travel in massive packs and are technically called Freakers (they are fast zombies). It's one of the weaker games from PlayStation Studios from the last decade, but there's still fun to be had and <em>lots </em>of zombies to run over with Deacon St. John's motorcycle. The Last of Part I, meanwhile, is a great remake of one of the most beloved PlayStation games of all time. It has revamped mechanics inspired by The Last of Us Part II and updated graphics. The Last of Us Part I is on sale for. only $32.39 (was $60), so now's a good time to add it to your Steam library.</p><p>Frightfest also includes some notable deals on hit indie games published by Devolver Digital. <strong><a href="https://clicks.trx-hub.com/xid/fandom_32094_gamespot?q=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jdoqocy.com%2Fclick-100770772-13797872%3Fsid%3Dsubid_value%26url%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.fanatical.com%2Fen%2Fgame%2Fcult-of-the-lamb&amp;p=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamespot.com%2Farticles%2Fhorror-game-sale-features-scary-good-deals-on-silent-hill-2-cult-of-the-lamb-and-more%2F1100-6527424%2F%3Fftag%3DCAD-01-10abi2f&amp;event_type=click" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Cult of the Lamb</a></strong>, which is almost certainly the funniest game about running a cult ever made, is up for grabs for 50% off. If you like action-RPGs, rogue-likes, or base management games, you should definitely give it a try. Rogue-like enthusiasts who haven't played the unique and unsettling deck-building game <strong><a href="https://clicks.trx-hub.com/xid/fandom_32094_gamespot?q=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dpbolvw.net%2Fclick-100770772-13797872%3Fsid%3Dsubid_value%26url%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.fanatical.com%2Fen%2Fgame%2Finscryption&amp;p=http